race.description: Australian Vaccine Services Class 1 & Maiden Plate
race.comment: VASALA (4) drops in grade and weight deep into the prep after finishing a plugging fifth over 1900m at Canterbury in BM64 class. Leading apprentice hops aboard and will push forward and take catching. CALL ME SON (1) jumped out to this trip for the first time when raced on the pace for a fighting third over 2100m at Gosford. Fitter now and Gibbons sticks. Solid top-three player. LA MORRA (10) sharp improver when getting off the mark at start six over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Jumps quickly in trip and stays in the calculations. O CARA MIA (6) forced to do a stack of work early from the outside draw when a wilting ninth over 1600m at Warwick Farm. Earlier runs had merit and gets map favours today. Each way. ICON DREAM (11) unlucky not to have already shed her Maiden tag. Proven at the trip and keep safe.
